file","alias":0}],"dname":"cashcraig","ctime_ts":1454449774,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/125607998/77081656","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/469987.html?thread=23942627#t23942627","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/469987.html?thread=23942627#t23942627","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/469987.html?thread=23942627#t23942627","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"thepainyak","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://thepainyak.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":23942627,"talkid":93525,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/469987.html?thread=23942627#t23942627","upictitle":"thepainyak: pic#125607998","article":"<i>\"Be warned: this one is not for the faint of heart. This is our horror book, and things get pretty horrible. Mayhem and madness and murder, oh my. Don't say I didn't warn you.\"</i> <br /><br />One of the great tragedies of growing older is the steady loss of the ability of things to horrify you, at least in fiction. <br /><br />When I was a kid, I was traumatized for days by the TV mini-series of Stephen King's IT. When I took a shower or bath, I kept imagining a clown rising from the drain and dragging me into the sewer to be devoured.<br /><br />Now, when I think on that possibility, I mostly reflect that that would be a pretty interesting way to go. Cancer, heart disease, car accidents...all very common. But how many people get to be eaten by an eldritch abomination disguised as a clown? If you've gotta go, it might as well be in a very memorable way. <br /><br />All of this is a long way of saying: Do your worst.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"February 2 2016, 21:52:36 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://thepai